{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"As an architect you design for the present,"},{"time":7000,"text":"with an awareness of the past,"},{"time":10000,"text":"for a future which is essentially unknown."},{"time":17000,"text":"The green agenda is probably the most important agenda"},{"time":21000,"text":"and issue of the day."},{"time":24000,"text":"And I'd like to share some experience"},{"time":28000,"text":"over the last 40 years -- we celebrate our fortieth anniversary this year --"},{"time":33000,"text":"and to explore and to touch on some observations"},{"time":39000,"text":"about the nature of sustainability."},{"time":43000,"text":"How far you can anticipate, what follows from it,"},{"time":46000,"text":"what are the threats, what are the possibilities,"},{"time":48000,"text":"the challenges, the opportunities?"},{"time":51000,"text":"I think that -- I've said in the past, many, many years ago,"},{"time":55000,"text":"before anybody even invented the concept of a green agenda,"},{"time":61000,"text":"that it wasn't about fashion -- it was about survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"But what I never said, and what I'm really going to make the point is,"},{"time":72000,"text":"that really, green is cool."},{"time":75000,"text":"I mean, all the projects which have, in some way, been inspired"},{"time":80000,"text":"by that agenda are about a celebratory lifestyle,"},{"time":85000,"text":"in a way celebrating the places and the spaces"},{"time":90000,"text":"which determine the quality of life."},{"time":93000,"text":"I rarely actually quote anything,"},{"time":97000,"text":"so I'm going to try and find a piece of paper if I can,"},{"time":101000,"text":"[in] which somebody, at the end of last year, ventured the thought"},{"time":107000,"text":"about what for that individual, as a kind of important observer,"},{"time":112000,"text":"analyst, writer -- a guy called Thomas Friedman,"},{"time":116000,"text":"who wrote in the Herald Tribune, about 2006."},{"time":122000,"text":"He said,"},{"time":125000,"text":"\"I think the most important thing to happen in 2006"},{"time":128000,"text":"was that living and thinking green hit Main Street."},{"time":133000,"text":"We reached a tipping point this year"},{"time":136000,"text":"where living, acting, designing, investing and manufacturing green"},{"time":141000,"text":"came to be understood by a critical mass"},{"time":143000,"text":"of citizens, entrepreneurs and officials"},{"time":146000,"text":"as the most patriotic, capitalistic, geo-political"},{"time":149000,"text":"and competitive thing they could do."},{"time":152000,"text":"Hence my motto: green is the new red, white and blue.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":158000,"text":"And I asked myself, in a way, looking back,"},{"time":162000,"text":"\"When did that kind of awareness of the planet and its fragility first appear?\""},{"time":172000,"text":"And I think it was July 20, 1969,"},{"time":176000,"text":"when, for the first time, man could look back at planet Earth."},{"time":182000,"text":"And, in a way, it was Buckminster Fuller who coined that phrase."},{"time":188000,"text":"And before the kind of collapse of the communist system,"},{"time":194000,"text":"I was privileged to meet a lot of cosmonauts"},{"time":197000,"text":"in Space City and other places in Russia."},{"time":199000,"text":"And interestingly, as I think back,"},{"time":202000,"text":"they were the first true environmentalists."},{"time":206000,"text":"They were filled with a kind of pioneering passion,"},{"time":211000,"text":"fired about the problems of the Aral Sea."},{"time":214000,"text":"And at that period it was --"},{"time":217000,"text":"in a way, a number of things were happening."},{"time":219000,"text":"Buckminster Fuller was the kind of green guru --"},{"time":224000,"text":"again, a word that had not been coined."},{"time":226000,"text":"He was a design scientist, if you like, a poet,"},{"time":230000,"text":"but he foresaw all the things that are happening now."},{"time":234000,"text":"It's another subject. It's another conversation."},{"time":237000,"text":"You can go back to his writings: it's quite extraordinary."},{"time":242000,"text":"It was at that time, with an awareness"},{"time":247000,"text":"fired by Bucky's prophecies, his concerns"},{"time":252000,"text":"as a citizen, as a kind of citizen of the planet,"},{"time":257000,"text":"that influenced my thinking and what we were doing at that time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"And it's a number of projects."},{"time":264000,"text":"I select this one because it was 1973, and it was a master plan"},{"time":270000,"text":"for one of the Canary Islands."},{"time":272000,"text":"And this probably coincided with the time"},{"time":276000,"text":"when you had the planet Earth's sourcebook,"},{"time":279000,"text":"and you had the hippie movement."},{"time":281000,"text":"And there are some of those qualities in this drawing,"},{"time":285000,"text":"which seeks to sum up the recommendations."},{"time":288000,"text":"And all the components are there which are now"},{"time":291000,"text":"in common parlance, in our vocabulary,"},{"time":294000,"text":"you know, 30-odd years later:"},{"time":297000,"text":"wind energy, recycling, biomass, solar cells."},{"time":302000,"text":"And in parallel at that time, there was"},{"time":306000,"text":"a very kind of exclusive design club."},{"time":311000,"text":"People who were really design conscious"},{"time":314000,"text":"were inspired by the work of Dieter Rams,"},{"time":317000,"text":"and the objects that he would create"},{"time":320000,"text":"for the company called Braun."},{"time":322000,"text":"This is going back the mid-'50s, '60s."},{"time":325000,"text":"And despite Bucky's prophecies"},{"time":328000,"text":"that everything would be miniaturized"},{"time":331000,"text":"and technology would make an incredible style --"},{"time":334000,"text":"access to comfort, to amenities --"},{"time":338000,"text":"it was very, very difficult to imagine"},{"time":341000,"text":"that everything that we see in this image,"},{"time":343000,"text":"would be very, very stylishly packaged."},{"time":346000,"text":"And that, and more besides, would be in the palm of your hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"And I think that that digital revolution"},{"time":353000,"text":"now is coming to the point"},{"time":356000,"text":"where, as the virtual world, which brings so many people together here,"},{"time":362000,"text":"finally connects with the physical world,"},{"time":364000,"text":"there is the reality that that has become humanized,"},{"time":370000,"text":"so that digital world has all the friendliness,"},{"time":374000,"text":"all the immediacy, the orientation of the analog world."},{"time":378000,"text":"Probably summed up in a way"},{"time":380000,"text":"by the stylish or alternative available here,"},{"time":384000,"text":"as we generously had gifted at lunchtime,"},{"time":388000,"text":"the [unclear], which is a further kind of development --"},{"time":392000,"text":"and again, inspired by the incredible sort of sensual feel."},{"time":396000,"text":"A very, very beautiful object."},{"time":398000,"text":"So, something which in [the] '50s, '60s was very exclusive"},{"time":403000,"text":"has now become, interestingly, quite inclusive."},{"time":406000,"text":"And the reference to the iPod as iconic,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and in a way evocative of performance, delivery --"},{"time":415000,"text":"quite interesting that [in] the beginning of the year 2007,"},{"time":418000,"text":"the Financial Times commented that the Detroit companies"},{"time":422000,"text":"envy the halo effect that Toyota has gained"},{"time":425000,"text":"from the Prius as the hybrid, energy-conscious vehicle,"},{"time":430000,"text":"which rivals the iPod as an iconic product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"And I think it's very tempting to, in a way, seduce ourselves --"},{"time":437000,"text":"as architects, or anybody involved with the design process --"},{"time":440000,"text":"that the answer to our problems lies with buildings."},{"time":444000,"text":"Buildings are important, but"},{"time":446000,"text":"they're only a component of a much bigger picture."},{"time":449000,"text":"In other words, as I might seek to demonstrate,"},{"time":451000,"text":"if you could achieve the impossible,"},{"time":453000,"text":"the equivalent of perpetual motion,"},{"time":456000,"text":"you could design a carbon-free house, for example."},{"time":460000,"text":"That would be the answer."},{"time":461000,"text":"Unfortunately, it's not the answer."},{"time":463000,"text":"It's only the beginning of the problem."},{"time":465000,"text":"You cannot separate the buildings out"},{"time":467000,"text":"from the infrastructure of cites"},{"time":469000,"text":"and the mobility of transit."},{"time":471000,"text":"For example, if, in that Bucky-inspired phrase, we draw back"},{"time":477000,"text":"and we look at planet Earth,"},{"time":479000,"text":"and we take a kind of typical, industrialized society,"},{"time":482000,"text":"then the energy consumed would be split"},{"time":485000,"text":"between the buildings, 44 percent, transport, 34 percent, and industry."},{"time":491000,"text":"But again, that only shows part of the picture."},{"time":493000,"text":"If you looked at the buildings together with the associated transport,"},{"time":498000,"text":"in other words, the transport of people, which is 26 percent,"},{"time":503000,"text":"then 70 percent of the energy consumption"},{"time":505000,"text":"is influenced by the way that our cites and infrastructure work together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"So the problems of sustainability"},{"time":515000,"text":"cannot be separated from the nature of the cities,"},{"time":518000,"text":"of which the buildings are a part."},{"time":521000,"text":"For example, if you take, and you make a comparison"},{"time":525000,"text":"between a recent kind of city,"},{"time":529000,"text":"what I'll call, simplistically, a North American city --"},{"time":532000,"text":"and Detroit is not a bad example, it is very car dependent."},{"time":537000,"text":"The city goes out in annular rings,"},{"time":540000,"text":"consuming more and more green space,"},{"time":542000,"text":"and more and more roads, and more and more energy"},{"time":546000,"text":"in the transport of people between the city center --"},{"time":550000,"text":"which again, the city center, as it becomes deprived"},{"time":553000,"text":"of the living and just becomes commercial, again becomes dead."},{"time":558000,"text":"If you compared Detroit with a city of a Northern European example --"},{"time":564000,"text":"and Munich is not a bad example of that,"},{"time":568000,"text":"with the greater dependence on walking and cycling --"},{"time":573000,"text":"then a city which is really only twice as dense,"},{"time":579000,"text":"is only using one-tenth of the energy."},{"time":583000,"text":"In other words, you take these comparable examples"},{"time":585000,"text":"and the energy leap is enormous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"So basically, if you wanted to generalize, you can demonstrate"},{"time":595000,"text":"that as the density increases along the bottom there,"},{"time":600000,"text":"that the energy consumed reduces dramatically."},{"time":604000,"text":"Of course you can't separate this out from issues like"},{"time":607000,"text":"social diversity, mass transit,"},{"time":610000,"text":"the ability to be able to walk a convenient distance,"},{"time":614000,"text":"the quality of civic spaces."},{"time":616000,"text":"But again, you can see Detroit, in yellow at the top,"},{"time":621000,"text":"extraordinary consumption, down below Copenhagen."},{"time":624000,"text":"And Copenhagen, although it's a dense city,"},{"time":626000,"text":"is not dense compared with the really dense cities."},{"time":631000,"text":"In the year 2000, a rather interesting thing happened."},{"time":636000,"text":"You had for the first time mega-cities, [of] 5 million or more,"},{"time":640000,"text":"which were occurring in the developing world."},{"time":644000,"text":"And now, out of typically 46 cities,"},{"time":647000,"text":"33 of those mega-cities are in the developing world."},{"time":652000,"text":"So you have to ask yourself -- the environmental impact of,"},{"time":656000,"text":"for example, China or India."},{"time":658000,"text":"If you take China, and you just take Beijing,"},{"time":663000,"text":"you can see on that traffic system,"},{"time":666000,"text":"and the pollution associated with the consumption of energy"},{"time":672000,"text":"as the cars expand at the price of the bicycles."},{"time":679000,"text":"In other words, if you put onto the roads, as is currently happening,"},{"time":684000,"text":"1,000 new cars every day --"},{"time":688000,"text":"statistically, it's the biggest booming auto market in the world --"},{"time":694000,"text":"and the half a billion bicycles serving one and a third billion people are reducing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"And that urbanization is extraordinary, accelerated pace."},{"time":709000,"text":"So, if we think of the transition in our society"},{"time":716000,"text":"of the movement from the land to the cities, which took 200 years,"},{"time":721000,"text":"then that same process is happening in 20 years."},{"time":726000,"text":"In other words, it is accelerating by a factor of 10."},{"time":731000,"text":"And quite interestingly, over something like a 60-year period,"},{"time":739000,"text":"we're seeing the doubling in life expectancy,"},{"time":742000,"text":"over that period where the urbanization has trebled."},{"time":748000,"text":"If I pull back from that global picture,"},{"time":751000,"text":"and I look at the implication over a similar period of time"},{"time":755000,"text":"in terms of the technology -- which, as a tool,"},{"time":759000,"text":"is a tool for designers,"},{"time":761000,"text":"and I cite our own experience as a company,"},{"time":765000,"text":"and I just illustrate that by a small selection of projects --"},{"time":770000,"text":"then how do you measure that change of technology?"},{"time":775000,"text":"How does it affect the design of buildings?"},{"time":778000,"text":"And particularly, how can it lead"},{"time":781000,"text":"to the creation of buildings which consume less energy,"},{"time":785000,"text":"create less pollution and are more socially responsible?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":790000,"text":"That story, in terms of buildings, started in the late '60s, early '70s."},{"time":796000,"text":"The one example I take is a corporate headquarters"},{"time":799000,"text":"for a company called Willis and Faber,"},{"time":802000,"text":"in a small market town in the northeast of England,"},{"time":809000,"text":"commuting distance with London."},{"time":812000,"text":"And here, the first thing you can see"},{"time":814000,"text":"is that this building, the roof is a very warm kind of"},{"time":819000,"text":"overcoat blanket, a kind of insulating garden,"},{"time":822000,"text":"which is also about the celebration of public space."},{"time":826000,"text":"In other words, for this community, they have this garden in the sky."},{"time":830000,"text":"So the humanistic ideal is very, very strong in all this work,"},{"time":835000,"text":"encapsulated perhaps by one of my early sketches here,"},{"time":840000,"text":"where you can see greenery, you can see sunlight,"},{"time":843000,"text":"you have a connection with nature."},{"time":845000,"text":"And nature is part of the generator, the driver for this building."},{"time":850000,"text":"And symbolically, the colors of the interior are green and yellow."},{"time":854000,"text":"It has facilities like swimming pools, it has flextime,"},{"time":858000,"text":"it has a social heart, a space, you have contact with nature."},{"time":863000,"text":"Now this was 1973."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866000,"text":"In 2001, this building received an award."},{"time":870000,"text":"And the award was about a celebration for a building"},{"time":873000,"text":"which had been in use over a long period of time."},{"time":877000,"text":"And the people who'd created it came back:"},{"time":880000,"text":"the project managers, the company chairmen then."},{"time":884000,"text":"And they were saying, you know,"},{"time":885000,"text":"\"The architects, Norman was always going on about"},{"time":888000,"text":"designing for the future, and you know,"},{"time":890000,"text":"it didn't seem to cost us any more."},{"time":892000,"text":"So we humored him, we kept him happy.\""},{"time":896000,"text":"The image at the top,"},{"time":898000,"text":"what it doesn't -- if you look at it in detail,"},{"time":900000,"text":"really what it is saying is you can wire this building."},{"time":904000,"text":"This building was wired for change."},{"time":908000,"text":"So, in 1975, the image there is of typewriters."},{"time":912000,"text":"And when the photograph was taken, it's word processors."},{"time":917000,"text":"And what they were saying on this occasion was that our competitors"},{"time":921000,"text":"had to build new buildings for the new technology."},{"time":925000,"text":"We were fortunate,"},{"time":927000,"text":"because in a way our building was future-proofed."},{"time":929000,"text":"It anticipated change, even though those changes were not known."},{"time":935000,"text":"Round about that design period leading up to this building,"},{"time":939000,"text":"I did a sketch, which we pulled out of the archive recently."},{"time":944000,"text":"And I was saying, and I wrote, \"But we don't have the time,"},{"time":948000,"text":"and we really don't have the immediate expertise"},{"time":951000,"text":"at a technical level.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"In other words, we didn't have the technology"},{"time":954000,"text":"to do what would be really interesting on that building."},{"time":958000,"text":"And that would be to create a kind of three-dimensional bubble --"},{"time":962000,"text":"a really interesting overcoat that would naturally ventilate,"},{"time":967000,"text":"would breathe and would seriously reduce the energy loads."},{"time":972000,"text":"Notwithstanding the fact that the building, as a green building,"},{"time":975000,"text":"is very much a pioneering building."},{"time":977000,"text":"And if I fast-forward in time, what is interesting"},{"time":980000,"text":"is that the technology is now available and celebratory."},{"time":985000,"text":"The library of the Free University, which opened last year,"},{"time":991000,"text":"is an example of that."},{"time":993000,"text":"And again, the transition from one of the many thousands"},{"time":997000,"text":"of sketches and computer images to the reality."},{"time":1001000,"text":"And a combination of devices here,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"the kind of heavy mass concrete of these book stacks,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and the way in which that is enclosed by this skin,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"which enables the building to be ventilated,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"to consume dramatically less energy,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"and where it's really working with the forces of nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023000,"text":"And what is interesting is that this is hugely popular"},{"time":1029000,"text":"by the people who use it."},{"time":1031000,"text":"Again, coming back to that thing about the lifestyle,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"and in a way, the ecological agenda is very much at one with the spirit."},{"time":1043000,"text":"So it's not a kind of sacrifice, quite the reverse."},{"time":1046000,"text":"I think it's a great -- it's a celebration."},{"time":1049000,"text":"And you can measure the performance,"},{"time":1053000,"text":"in terms of energy consumption, of that building"},{"time":1056000,"text":"against a typical library."},{"time":1059000,"text":"If I show another aspect of that technology"},{"time":1062000,"text":"then, in a completely different context --"},{"time":1066000,"text":"this apartment building in the Alps in Switzerland."},{"time":1071000,"text":"Prefabricated from the most traditional of materials,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"but that material -- because of the technology, the computing ability,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"the ability to prefabricate, make high-performance components"},{"time":1083000,"text":"out of timber -- very much at the cutting edge."},{"time":1087000,"text":"And just to give a sort of glimpse of that technology,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"the ability to plot points in the sky"},{"time":1098000,"text":"and to transmit, to transfer that information"},{"time":1105000,"text":"now, directly into the factory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1110000,"text":"So if you cross the border -- just across the border --"},{"time":1113000,"text":"a small factory in Germany, and here you can see the guy with his computer screen,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"and those points in space are communicated."},{"time":1123000,"text":"And on the left are the cutting machines,"},{"time":1126000,"text":"which then, in the factory,"},{"time":1128000,"text":"enable those individual pieces to be fabricated"},{"time":1132000,"text":"and plus or minus very, very few millimeters,"},{"time":1135000,"text":"to be slotted together on site."},{"time":1138000,"text":"And then interestingly, that building to then be clad"},{"time":1144000,"text":"in the oldest technology, which is the kind of hand-cut shingles."},{"time":1150000,"text":"One quarter of a million of them applied by hand as the final finish."},{"time":1157000,"text":"And again, the way in which that works as a building,"},{"time":1161000,"text":"for those of us who can enjoy the spaces,"},{"time":1165000,"text":"to live and visit there."},{"time":1168000,"text":"If I made the leap into these new technologies,"},{"time":1172000,"text":"then how did we -- what happened before that?"},{"time":1175000,"text":"I mean, you know, what was life like before the mobile phone,"},{"time":1181000,"text":"the things that you take for granted?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184000,"text":"Well, obviously the building still happened."},{"time":1186000,"text":"I mean, this is a glimpse of the interior of our Hong Kong bank of 1979,"},{"time":1194000,"text":"which opened in 1985, with the ability to be able to reflect sunlight"},{"time":1199000,"text":"deep into the heart of this space here."},{"time":1202000,"text":"And in the absence of computers, you have to physically model."},{"time":1206000,"text":"So for example, we would put models under an artificial sky."},{"time":1213000,"text":"For wind tunnels, we would literally put them"},{"time":1215000,"text":"in a wind tunnel and blast air,"},{"time":1218000,"text":"and the many kilometers of cable and so on."},{"time":1222000,"text":"And the turning point was probably, in our terms,"},{"time":1226000,"text":"when we had the first computer."},{"time":1230000,"text":"And that was at the time that we sought"},{"time":1234000,"text":"to redesign, reinvent the airport."},{"time":1238000,"text":"This is Terminal Four at Heathrow, typical of any terminal --"},{"time":1243000,"text":"big, heavy roof, blocking out the sunlight,"},{"time":1245000,"text":"lots of machinery, big pipes, whirring machinery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1250000,"text":"And Stansted, the green alternative,"},{"time":1255000,"text":"which uses natural light, is a friendly place:"},{"time":1257000,"text":"you know where you are, you can relate to the outside."},{"time":1261000,"text":"And for a large part of its cycle, not needing electric light --"},{"time":1265000,"text":"electric light, which in turn creates more heat,"},{"time":1268000,"text":"which creates more cooling loads and so on."},{"time":1270000,"text":"And at that particular point in time,"},{"time":1273000,"text":"this was one of the few solitary computers."},{"time":1277000,"text":"And that's a little image of the tree of Stansted."},{"time":1283000,"text":"Not going back very far in time, 1990,"},{"time":1286000,"text":"that's our office."},{"time":1289000,"text":"And if you looked very closely, you'd see"},{"time":1292000,"text":"that people were drawing with pencils,"},{"time":1294000,"text":"and they were pushing, you know, big rulers and triangles."},{"time":1298000,"text":"It's not that long ago, 17 years, and here we are now."},{"time":1302000,"text":"I mean, major transformation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1305000,"text":"Going back in time, there was a lady called Valerie Larkin,"},{"time":1309000,"text":"and in 1987, she had all our information on one disk."},{"time":1316000,"text":"Now, every week, we have the equivalent of 84 million disks,"},{"time":1325000,"text":"which record our archival information"},{"time":1328000,"text":"on past, current and future projects."},{"time":1331000,"text":"That reaches 21 kilometers into the sky."},{"time":1335000,"text":"This is the view you would get, if you looked down on that."},{"time":1338000,"text":"But meanwhile, as you know,"},{"time":1340000,"text":"wonderful protagonists like Al Gore"},{"time":1344000,"text":"are noting the inexorable rise in temperature,"},{"time":1350000,"text":"set in the context of that,"},{"time":1353000,"text":"interestingly, those buildings which are celebratory"},{"time":1355000,"text":"and very, very relevant to this place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1359000,"text":"Our Reichstag project,"},{"time":1362000,"text":"which has a very familiar agenda, I'm sure,"},{"time":1366000,"text":"as a public place where we sought to, in a way,"},{"time":1372000,"text":"through a process of advocacy,"},{"time":1375000,"text":"reinterpret the relationship between society and politicians,"},{"time":1380000,"text":"public space. And maybe its hidden agenda, an energy manifesto --"},{"time":1385000,"text":"something that would be free, completely free"},{"time":1388000,"text":"of fuel as we know it."},{"time":1391000,"text":"So it would be totally renewable."},{"time":1393000,"text":"And again, the humanistic sketch, the translation into the public space,"},{"time":1398000,"text":"but this very, very much a part of the ecology."},{"time":1401000,"text":"But here, not having to model it for real."},{"time":1405000,"text":"Obviously the wind tunnel had a place,"},{"time":1408000,"text":"but the ability now with the computer"},{"time":1410000,"text":"to explore, to plan, to see how that would work"},{"time":1414000,"text":"in terms of the forces of nature:"},{"time":1416000,"text":"natural ventilation, to be able to model the chamber below,"},{"time":1420000,"text":"and to look at biomass."},{"time":1423000,"text":"A combination of biomass, aquifers, burning vegetable oil --"},{"time":1430000,"text":"a process that, quite interestingly, was developed"},{"time":1434000,"text":"in Eastern Germany, at the time of its"},{"time":1438000,"text":"dependence on the Soviet Bloc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1440000,"text":"So really, retranslating that technology and developing something"},{"time":1444000,"text":"which was so clean, it was virtually pollution-free."},{"time":1448000,"text":"You can measure it again."},{"time":1449000,"text":"You can compare how that building, in terms of its emission"},{"time":1453000,"text":"in tons of carbon dioxide per year --"},{"time":1455000,"text":"at the time that we took that project, over 7,000 tons --"},{"time":1459000,"text":"what it would have been with natural gas"},{"time":1460000,"text":"and finally, with the vegetable oil, 450 tons."},{"time":1463000,"text":"I mean, a 94 percent reduction -- virtually clean."},{"time":1466000,"text":"We can see the same processes at work"},{"time":1468000,"text":"in terms of the Commerce Bank --"},{"time":1470000,"text":"its dependence on natural ventilation,"},{"time":1472000,"text":"the way that you can model those gardens,"},{"time":1474000,"text":"the way they spiral around."},{"time":1476000,"text":"But again, very much about the lifestyle, the quality --"},{"time":1480000,"text":"something that would be more enjoyable as a place to work."},{"time":1484000,"text":"And again, we can measure the reduction"},{"time":1486000,"text":"in terms of energy consumption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1490000,"text":"There is an evolution here between the projects,"},{"time":1492000,"text":"and Swiss Re again develops that a little bit further --"},{"time":1497000,"text":"the project in the city in London."},{"time":1499000,"text":"And this sequence shows the buildup of that model."},{"time":1503000,"text":"But what it shows first, which I think is quite interesting,"},{"time":1506000,"text":"is that here you see the circle, you see the public space around it."},{"time":1511000,"text":"What are the other ways of putting"},{"time":1513000,"text":"the same amount of space on the site?"},{"time":1516000,"text":"If, for example, you seek to do a building"},{"time":1520000,"text":"which goes right to the edge of the pavement,"},{"time":1525000,"text":"it's the same amount of space."},{"time":1528000,"text":"And finally, you profile this, you cut grooves into it."},{"time":1533000,"text":"The grooves become the kind of green lungs"},{"time":1536000,"text":"which give views, which give light, ventilation,"},{"time":1540000,"text":"make the building fresher."},{"time":1542000,"text":"And you enclose that with something that also"},{"time":1545000,"text":"is central to its appearance,"},{"time":1548000,"text":"which is a mesh of triangulated structures --"},{"time":1552000,"text":"again, in a long connection evocative of"},{"time":1555000,"text":"some of those works of Buckminster Fuller,"},{"time":1558000,"text":"and the way in which triangulation can increase performance"},{"time":1562000,"text":"and also give that building its sense of identity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1567000,"text":"And here, if we look at a detail of the way"},{"time":1570000,"text":"that the building opens up and breathes into those atria,"},{"time":1573000,"text":"the way in which now, with a computer, we can model the forces,"},{"time":1578000,"text":"we can see the high pressure, the low pressure,"},{"time":1581000,"text":"the way in which the building behaves rather like an aircraft wing."},{"time":1585000,"text":"So it also has the ability, all the time,"},{"time":1588000,"text":"regardless of the direction of the wind,"},{"time":1590000,"text":"to be able to make the building fresh and efficient."},{"time":1595000,"text":"And unlike conventional buildings,"},{"time":1598000,"text":"the top of the building is celebratory."},{"time":1600000,"text":"It's a viewing place for people, not machinery."},{"time":1603000,"text":"And the base of the building is again about public space."},{"time":1607000,"text":"Comparing it with a typical building,"},{"time":1609000,"text":"what happens if we seek to use such design strategies"},{"time":1614000,"text":"in terms of really large-scale thinking?"},{"time":1618000,"text":"And I'm just going to give two images"},{"time":1620000,"text":"out of a kind of company research project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1626000,"text":"It's been well known that the Dead Sea is dying."},{"time":1632000,"text":"The level is dropping, rather like the Aral Sea."},{"time":1636000,"text":"And the Dead Sea is obviously much lower"},{"time":1640000,"text":"than the oceans and seas around it."},{"time":1644000,"text":"So there has been a project which rescues the Dead Sea"},{"time":1648000,"text":"by creating a pipeline, a pipe,"},{"time":1652000,"text":"sometimes above the surface, sometimes buried,"},{"time":1655000,"text":"that will redress that, and will feed from the Gulf of Aqaba"},{"time":1661000,"text":"into the Dead Sea."},{"time":1663000,"text":"And our translation of that,"},{"time":1664000,"text":"using a lot of the thinking built up over the 40 years, is to say,"},{"time":1669000,"text":"what if that, instead of being just a pipe,"},{"time":1672000,"text":"what if it is a lifeline?"},{"time":1674000,"text":"What if it is the equivalent, depending on where you are,"},{"time":1678000,"text":"of the Grand Canal,"},{"time":1680000,"text":"in terms of tourists, habitation, desalination, agriculture?"},{"time":1685000,"text":"In other words, water is the lifeblood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1687000,"text":"And if you just go back to the previous image,"},{"time":1690000,"text":"and you look at this area of volatility and hostility,"},{"time":1694000,"text":"that a unifying design idea as a humanitarian gesture"},{"time":1700000,"text":"could have the affect of bringing all those warring factions together"},{"time":1704000,"text":"in a united cause, in terms of something that would be"},{"time":1708000,"text":"genuinely green and productive in the widest sense."},{"time":1714000,"text":"Infrastructure at that large scale is also"},{"time":1716000,"text":"inseparable from communication."},{"time":1721000,"text":"And whether that communication is the virtual world"},{"time":1724000,"text":"or it is the physical world,"},{"time":1725000,"text":"then it's absolutely central to society."},{"time":1728000,"text":"And how do we make more legible in this growing world,"},{"time":1733000,"text":"especially in some of the places that I'm talking about --"},{"time":1737000,"text":"China, for example, which in the next ten years"},{"time":1739000,"text":"will create 400 new airports."},{"time":1743000,"text":"Now what form do they take?"},{"time":1745000,"text":"How do you make them more friendly at that scale?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1748000,"text":"Hong Kong I refer to as a kind of analog experience in a digital age,"},{"time":1755000,"text":"because you always have a point of reference."},{"time":1757000,"text":"So what happens when we take that and you expand that further"},{"time":1763000,"text":"into the Chinese society?"},{"time":1767000,"text":"And what is interesting is that that produces in a way"},{"time":1771000,"text":"perhaps the ultimate mega-building."},{"time":1773000,"text":"It is physically the largest project on the planet at the moment."},{"time":1777000,"text":"250 -- excuse me, 50,000 people working 24 hours, seven days."},{"time":1783000,"text":"Larger by 17 percent than every terminal put together"},{"time":1787000,"text":"at Heathrow -- built -- plus the new, un-built Terminal Five."},{"time":1792000,"text":"And the challenge here is a building that will be green,"},{"time":1796000,"text":"that is compact despite its size"},{"time":1799000,"text":"and is about the human experience of travel,"},{"time":1804000,"text":"is about friendly, is coming back to that starting point,"},{"time":1809000,"text":"is very, very much about the lifestyle."},{"time":1811000,"text":"And perhaps these, in the end, as celebratory spaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1817000,"text":"As Hubert was talking over lunch,"},{"time":1819000,"text":"as we sort of engaged in conversation,"},{"time":1821000,"text":"talked about this, talked about cities."},{"time":1823000,"text":"Hubert was saying, absolutely correctly, \"These are the new cathedrals.\""},{"time":1828000,"text":"And in a way, one aspect of this conversation"},{"time":1832000,"text":"was triggered on New Year's Eve,"},{"time":1836000,"text":"when I was talking about the Olympic agenda in China"},{"time":1844000,"text":"in terms of its green ambitions and aspirations."},{"time":1849000,"text":"And I was voicing the thought that --"},{"time":1851000,"text":"it just crossed my mind that New Year's Eve,"},{"time":1853000,"text":"a sort of symbolic turning point as we move from 2006 to 2007 --"},{"time":1859000,"text":"that maybe, you know, the future was"},{"time":1861000,"text":"the most powerful, innovative sort of nation."},{"time":1865000,"text":"The way in which somebody like Kennedy inspirationally could say,"},{"time":1868000,"text":"\"We put a man on the moon.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1869000,"text":"You know, who is going to say"},{"time":1871000,"text":"that we cracked this thing of the dependence on fossil fuels,"},{"time":1876000,"text":"with all that being held to ransom by rogue regimes, and so on."},{"time":1880000,"text":"And that's a concerted platform."},{"time":1882000,"text":"It's more than one device, you know, it's renewable."},{"time":1885000,"text":"And I voiced the thought that maybe at the turn of the year,"},{"time":1889000,"text":"I thought that the inspiration was more likely"},{"time":1891000,"text":"to come from those other, larger countries out there --"},{"time":1893000,"text":"the Chinas, the Indias, the Asian-Pacific tigers."},{"time":1897000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1899000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}